Nitrate.name: Nitrate
Nitrate.description: Chemical that can come from fertilizer runoff, septic systems, or natural deposits
Nitrate.healthEffects: Especially dangerous for infants under 6 months - can cause "blue baby syndrome" (methemoglobinemia)
Nitrate.whatToDo: DO NOT BOIL - boiling increases nitrate concentration. Use bottled water for infant formula and drinking.

Lead.name: Lead
Lead.description: Toxic metal that can leach from plumbing materials
Lead.healthEffects: Can cause developmental delays in children and health problems in adults
Lead.whatToDo: Run cold water for 30 seconds before use. Consider water testing and filters certified for lead removal.

Copper.name: Copper
Copper.description: Metal that can leach from plumbing materials
Copper.healthEffects: Can cause gastrointestinal distress and liver or kidney damage
Copper.whatToDo: Run cold water before use. Test your water if you notice blue-green staining.

Lead and Copper Rule.name: Lead and Copper Rule
Lead and Copper Rule.description: Regulatory framework for monitoring lead and copper in drinking water
Lead and Copper Rule.healthEffects: Lead can cause developmental delays in children and health problems in adults
Lead and Copper Rule.whatToDo: Run cold water for 30 seconds before use. Consider water testing and filters certified for lead removal.
Lead and Copper Rule.mcl: Action Level: 0.015 mg/L Lead, 1.3 mg/L Copper

pH.name: pH
pH.description: Measure of water acidity or alkalinity
pH.healthEffects: Not directly harmful but can affect water taste and corrosion of pipes
pH.whatToDo: Usually not a concern for drinking. Contact your water system if pH is consistently outside normal range.

Total Dissolved Solids (TDS).name: Total Dissolved Solids (TDS)
Total Dissolved Solids (TDS).description: Total amount of dissolved minerals and salts in water
Total Dissolved Solids (TDS).healthEffects: Not directly harmful but can affect taste and indicate other problems
Total Dissolved Solids (TDS).whatToDo: Usually not a concern. High TDS may indicate need for water softening.

Atrazine.name: Atrazine
Atrazine.healthEffects: May cause cardiovascular and reproductive problems
Atrazine.whatToDo: Use activated carbon filters. Consider bottled water if levels are high.

Aldicarb.name: Aldicarb
Aldicarb.healthEffects: Can affect nervous system and cause nausea, dizziness
Aldicarb.whatToDo: Use activated carbon filters. Avoid drinking if levels are high.

Zinc.name: Zinc
Zinc.description: Metal that can leach from plumbing or occur naturally
Zinc.healthEffects: Essential nutrient but high levels can cause nausea and stomach cramps
Zinc.whatToDo: Usually not a concern. High levels may indicate plumbing corrosion.

Antimony.name: Antimony
Antimony.description: Metalloid element that can occur naturally or from industrial sources
Antimony.healthEffects: Can cause nausea, vomiting, and diarrhea
Antimony.whatToDo: Contact your water system if levels are high.

Nitrate-Nitrite.name: Nitrate-Nitrite
Nitrate-Nitrite.description: Combined measurement of nitrate and nitrite compounds
Nitrate-Nitrite.healthEffects: Especially dangerous for infants under 6 months - can cause "blue baby syndrome"
Nitrate-Nitrite.whatToDo: DO NOT BOIL - boiling increases nitrate concentration. Use bottled water for infant formula.

Asbestos.name: Asbestos
Asbestos.description: Fibrous mineral that can occur naturally in water
Asbestos.healthEffects: Can cause lung disease and cancer when inhaled
Asbestos.whatToDo: Contact your water system if asbestos is detected.

Chromium, Hexavalent.name: Chromium, Hexavalent
Chromium, Hexavalent.description: Toxic form of chromium that can occur naturally or from industrial sources
Chromium, Hexavalent.healthEffects: Can cause cancer and other health problems
Chromium, Hexavalent.whatToDo: Use reverse osmosis or ion exchange filters if levels are high.
